WEBVTT

00:04.226 --> 00:05.087
Welcome to Life Church.

00:05.488 --> 00:09.052
We're here to help you become who God created you to be, and we'd love to hear from you.

00:09.112 --> 00:15.620
Take a quick survey at life.church slash podcast connect to let us know how we can support you on your faith journey.

00:15.961 --> 00:17.302
And now let's go to the message.

00:22.409 --> 00:33.042
All right, so I am a little bitter, maybe a lot emotional because it was 30 years ago this weekend that a handful of people, many of you,

00:33.314 --> 00:37.159
met for the very first time in a two-car garage.

00:38.020 --> 00:45.930
And today, here we are three decades later celebrating God's faithfulness.

00:45.950 --> 00:46.731
God's goodness.

00:47.512 --> 00:49.134
God's power.

00:49.154 --> 00:50.095
God's grace.

00:50.896 --> 00:54.080
As Jesus has been building God's church.

00:54.781 --> 00:58.525
And today I celebrate the presence of God, the goodness of God.

00:58.545 --> 01:02.450
And honestly, I celebrate every single one of you, every life that has been changed.

01:02.754 --> 01:13.266
Everyone that's prayed faithfully, everyone that served and used their gifts, everyone who's given toward the work of God, people say, did you ever expect any of this to happen?

01:13.286 --> 01:14.107
And the answer is no.

01:14.127 --> 01:19.794
And if you told me it might, I probably would have run for the hills because it exceeds anything I ever dreamed possible.

01:19.834 --> 01:24.880
And so it's this time of the year that we tend to look back just at our own lives.

01:24.920 --> 01:30.066
I'm doing that in the church and we tend to look forward and we evaluate where have we been

01:30.466 --> 01:32.849
and where is God calling us to go?

01:33.770 --> 01:36.454
And if you're like most people, you're probably looking at your life right now.

01:36.494 --> 01:39.157
You might be making some goals moving forward.

01:39.177 --> 01:41.680
I'm doing that in my life and in the church as well.

01:42.602 --> 01:44.524
You might set goals to eat better this year.

01:44.584 --> 01:47.528
You might set goals to maybe eliminate debt.

01:48.028 --> 01:50.091
You might set goals to strengthen your marriage.

01:50.452 --> 01:52.154
All are really, really good goals.

01:52.975 --> 01:54.697
But I wanna raise the question today.

01:54.737 --> 01:58.642
What if our greatest goal this year

01:59.778 --> 02:01.961
wasn't just to improve our lives.

02:03.122 --> 02:07.648
But what if our greatest goal were to please God?

02:09.070 --> 02:20.584
Above anything else, what if the driving desire, the cry of our hearts is to live in such a way that our greatest goal is to please God?

02:21.565 --> 02:28.594
It was Paul who said this in 2 Corinthians chapter 5 verse 9, he said, so whether we're here in this body,

02:29.666 --> 02:32.850
Or away from this body, say it with you, what is our goal?

02:33.090 --> 02:36.234
Our goal is to please God.

02:36.695 --> 02:44.304
What if our greatest goal above anything else would be to live in such a way that our lives would please God?

02:45.946 --> 02:49.991
Above all else, what kind of church are we going to be?

02:50.872 --> 02:59.442
From day number one to 30 years in for as long as we're on this earth, it is my prayer that we are a church

02:59.874 --> 03:01.436
that pleases God.

03:02.538 --> 03:10.350
And if we're gonna be a church that pleases God, it's gotta be filled with people that are pleasing God.

03:11.131 --> 03:18.803
And that means you gotta please God, and I gotta please God, and we gotta individually please God, so corporately we would please God, and how are we gonna do that?

03:19.604 --> 03:28.498
Well, the Bible is very, very, very clear that there is one quality without which,

03:29.442 --> 03:35.789
It is impossible to please God, and we're gonna talk about it.

03:37.110 --> 03:42.115
But first, we're gonna pray and give God glory.

03:42.135 --> 03:43.777
Father, we love you, we honor you.

03:43.817 --> 03:46.319
Your name is the only one worthy of all praise.

03:47.821 --> 03:56.690
And today, God, we worship you for every person that's been saved, for every marriage healed,

03:57.538 --> 04:18.544
for every prodigal that came back to Jesus, for every bondage and change that's been broken, for every relationship that's been healed, for every single person who's been made new in Christ, who's found their place to serve as your church, in your church, to reach the world with your love.

04:19.585 --> 04:20.867
We give you the glory for it.

04:21.748 --> 04:23.730
And God, we believe that you want to do more.

04:24.482 --> 04:26.345
as where a church that honors you with faith.

04:26.405 --> 04:30.811
We pray this in Jesus name and all God's people said, amen, and amen.

04:31.752 --> 04:39.302
To be a church that pleases God, it's impossible to please God without this quality.

04:39.903 --> 04:41.926
Hebrews 11, 6 tells us this.

04:42.546 --> 04:43.227
And without what?

04:43.287 --> 04:44.489
Let's say it aloud as a church.

04:44.509 --> 04:46.211
I need everybody here, I need all of our campuses.

04:46.231 --> 04:47.113
There's no fun without you.

04:47.133 --> 04:48.494
Everybody everywhere, without what?

04:48.554 --> 04:52.500
Without faith, it's impossible to please God.

04:53.141 --> 04:54.162
To live a life

04:55.074 --> 05:02.367
Without trusting God boldly in faith, it's impossible to please God.

05:03.148 --> 05:08.257
If we're gonna be a church that pleases God, we have to be a faith-filled church, to be a faith-filled church.

05:08.578 --> 05:12.104
That means you need to live by faith, I need to live by faith.

05:12.124 --> 05:15.190
And to be clear, this doesn't just be like mountain-moving faith.

05:15.991 --> 05:20.018
Like, God, if you want me to take this job,

05:21.026 --> 05:23.529
May I camel walk in my room right now?

05:23.549 --> 05:25.491
We're not talking about just that kind of faith.

05:25.511 --> 05:30.717
Sometimes it's like God helped me love my boss today, faith, right?

05:31.638 --> 05:36.924
It's not just faith in the big moments, it's faith as a lifestyle.

05:36.944 --> 05:46.535
It's not just faith in the big decisions, but it's faith in the everyday decisions because it was the Apostle Paul that said this, he said, for we walk by what?

05:46.595 --> 05:49.138
We walk by faith and not by

05:49.282 --> 05:58.033
It's faith that when we wake up in the morning, we open up God's word believing that God wants to speak to us on that day.

05:58.074 --> 06:01.158
It's faith to believe that He'll direct our steps.

06:01.398 --> 06:08.727
It's faith to believe that His Spirit will prompt us to use our gifts to make a difference in the lives of others.

06:08.808 --> 06:12.913
It's faith to trust God even when we don't understand.

06:13.454 --> 06:16.818
It's the faith to believe what God says

06:17.186 --> 06:20.589
even when what he says is different than what we see.

06:20.649 --> 06:26.675
Without faith, it's impossible to please God.

06:27.556 --> 06:38.005
So I wanna ask you as you move into a new year, a very serious question I'm asking myself, and the question is this, is your faith pleasing to God?

06:39.907 --> 06:43.831
Are you believing God for supernatural works?

06:44.792 --> 06:47.154
Are you taking daily steps of faith?

06:47.938 --> 06:49.340
How big is your prayer life?

06:49.380 --> 06:50.321
I could ask it this way.

06:50.621 --> 06:56.027
If God answered every prayer you prayed last week, what would be different in the world?

06:58.249 --> 07:04.916
Was your food being blessed and you got to work safe or people be saved?

07:08.320 --> 07:09.581
Is your faith pleasing to God?

07:11.143 --> 07:17.490
What's interesting is the gospel shows us two examples of how Jesus

07:17.666 --> 07:19.268
responds to faith.

07:19.648 --> 07:22.991
Two examples of how Jesus responds to faith.

07:23.031 --> 07:25.033
The first one is in Mark chapter six.

07:25.674 --> 07:27.876
And Jesus was in his hometown.

07:28.156 --> 07:28.837
He was teaching.

07:29.257 --> 07:30.718
And so people were kind of offended.

07:30.738 --> 07:31.579
They were kind of critical.

07:31.619 --> 07:34.442
They were saying, hey, isn't this like the son of the carpenter?

07:34.462 --> 07:36.164
I mean, isn't that Joey's boy?

07:36.184 --> 07:38.086
I mean, we saw him grow up.

07:38.206 --> 07:41.789
Isn't that just that guy that's not that important?

07:41.809 --> 07:46.994
And they didn't honor Jesus and they didn't believe what he said

07:47.586 --> 07:48.507
was true.

07:49.248 --> 07:59.661
And in Mark 6, 6, the Bible says that Jesus was amazed at their lack of faith.

08:00.622 --> 08:03.626
Two times Jesus was amazed by faith.

08:03.806 --> 08:06.269
The first time he was amazed by a lack of faith.

08:06.850 --> 08:13.138
The second story is in Luke chapter 7, and there was this man whose servant was dying.

08:13.698 --> 08:15.620
And the man had a conversation with Jesus.

08:15.640 --> 08:18.663
And he said, Jesus, I'm summarizing and giving you my version.

08:18.683 --> 08:22.747
But you're so powerful and important that I don't wanna waste your time.

08:22.767 --> 08:24.829
You don't even have to go to where he is.

08:25.229 --> 08:31.275
Jesus, if you just say the word, my servant will be healed.

08:31.295 --> 08:32.456
And the Bible says this.

08:32.897 --> 08:38.482
When Jesus heard this, Luke seven, nine, he was again amazed at this man.

08:39.283 --> 08:42.546
And turning to the crowd following him, he said, I tell you,

08:42.946 --> 08:48.473
I have not found such great faith even in Israel.

08:50.316 --> 08:55.403
When it comes to faith, Jesus had two responses.

08:57.466 --> 09:02.573
One, Jesus was amazed by a lack of faith.

09:04.115 --> 09:08.861
And then Jesus was amazed by great faith.

09:11.485 --> 09:12.466
And so when I ask you,

09:13.794 --> 09:16.258
Which one is you?

09:18.281 --> 09:21.846
Is your faith pleasing to God?

09:21.866 --> 09:33.664
I want to tell you with great emotion and great gratitude to God, a little bit of my faith journey with Amy 30 years ago, starting live church.

09:34.706 --> 09:40.274
The first Sunday was this snowy cold Sunday morning.

09:41.090 --> 09:43.674
And I'm gonna tell you right now, I feel just like I do today.

09:43.714 --> 09:47.640
If I tell you what I'm getting up here, I literally, I'm as nervous today as I was back then.

09:47.660 --> 09:50.445
I used to throw up in a bucket back then.

09:50.485 --> 09:52.928
Now I've grown into things of the Lord.

09:53.069 --> 09:55.512
I just throw up in my mouth, I swallow it, and we're good to go.

09:55.573 --> 10:00.961
I've come so far, thank God, for sanctification by the power of the Holy Spirit.

10:00.981 --> 10:02.623
I'm in such a better place today.

10:02.984 --> 10:09.394
I was, I was, like at the same time, I don't know if you've ever been there, but I was full of faith, and I was so scared.

10:09.826 --> 10:12.549
I was full of faith, and I was insecure.

10:12.589 --> 10:14.651
I was only 28 years old.

10:14.911 --> 10:16.853
I couldn't even grow a real mustache.

10:18.174 --> 10:22.819
I didn't really want to, but the fact that I couldn't really bother me so much at the time.

10:23.239 --> 10:30.967
And for context, we had no building, no money at all, except for what Amy and I put in there, and it was a lot to us, but not much really.

10:31.587 --> 10:38.354
We had no staff, we had no plan B, and we met in a garage that someone let us meet in with borrowed chairs,

10:38.498 --> 10:40.521
And we had an overhead projector.

10:41.262 --> 10:49.713
Now, for those of you that were not born 30 years ago, you don't know what an overhead projector is, and you can just take a moment to praise God right now that you don't know what it is.

10:50.114 --> 11:08.178
But if you don't know, I'll tell you an overhead projector was a little machine that you would take a transparent piece of God, transparent sheet, and you'd write the words to the worship song, and you'd put it on this thing, and would transport it onto not a wall, not a screen, but onto the garage door.

11:08.770 --> 11:09.551
Because that's what we had.

11:09.972 --> 11:12.956
And what's pretty cool is our transparency flipper.

11:13.016 --> 11:15.499
That's a spiritual gift if you didn't know that.

11:15.860 --> 11:23.630
His name was Jerome and Jerome was a drug dealer that got a finger shot off in a drug deal that went bad.

11:24.191 --> 11:26.414
But by the grace of God, Jerome was made new.

11:26.915 --> 11:29.458
And so Jerome was what we call the four finger flipper.

11:30.114 --> 11:39.723
and he would flip the transparencies back and forth, and people would be trying to worship, but they'd recognize something looked odd, and you could see them going, praise God, one, two, three.

11:42.666 --> 11:43.046
Four.

11:44.147 --> 11:53.577
And what's amazing is, to the glory of God, 30 years later, Jerome still worships with us, happens to be on the front row, may raise even the correct hand if you want to, Jerome.

11:56.740 --> 11:57.741
Raise the correct hand, and can you zoom in on it?

11:57.761 --> 11:58.081
Can we zoom out?

11:58.101 --> 11:59.282
Look at that, look at that, one, two, three.

12:00.162 --> 12:00.743
Four.

12:03.826 --> 12:17.900
And 29 years ago, I had the honor of officiating the service between you and Shanna, who you had only dated a girl for a total of three weeks, and now you're married 29 years in, one of the most god-honoring evangelists that I've ever known.

12:17.960 --> 12:25.147
And in the middle of that, I was insecure and afraid.

12:25.167 --> 12:27.730
But all of us, we had faith.

12:28.738 --> 12:40.560
And the reason I had faith is because about 10 years earlier, I was a hurting and lost college student dead in my sins.

12:42.043 --> 12:50.098
And I called out on Jesus and said, if you're real and if you're there and if you can save me, save.

12:59.458 --> 13:08.147
And the work he did in my heart was something no man could do, but only by the grace of God.

13:08.247 --> 13:09.749
He set me free from addiction.

13:09.789 --> 13:11.070
He gave me purpose.

13:12.171 --> 13:12.792
He set me apart.

13:12.812 --> 13:17.857
He gave me peace and the strangest thing.

13:17.937 --> 13:22.482
I was a business major, but immediately I felt called to be a pastor.

13:22.783 --> 13:23.884
No reason whatsoever.

13:25.085 --> 13:26.066
None whatsoever.

13:26.306 --> 13:28.229
I didn't know a pastor I looked up to at the time.

13:28.269 --> 13:29.751
I didn't know a pastor I liked.

13:29.771 --> 13:33.397
I just, I felt called to be a pastor and I was too dumb to change my major to religion.

13:33.697 --> 13:35.019
And that I ended up paying for later.

13:35.200 --> 13:41.730
But I'm starting this new church in the middle of both faith and fear.

13:41.790 --> 13:48.580
We had about 40 people on that first Sunday and we had the faith that all things were possible to God.

13:49.141 --> 13:54.770
I'm telling you, I can just remember back then with nothing in the natural, we had faith that God would provide.

13:54.978 --> 13:56.119
with nothing in the natural.

13:56.139 --> 13:58.001
We get the faith that God is powerful.

13:58.242 --> 14:23.349
We have the faith to believe that His Word is living and active and powerful and sharper than any double-edged sword, and that when His Word is free-sliser, it's saying we have faith to believe that Jesus died and that God raised Him from the dead and the faith to believe that anyone who calls on the name of the Lord would be saved and redeemed and filled with the same spirit that raised Christ from the dead.

14:23.469 --> 14:24.370
Looking back,

14:24.482 --> 14:34.052
I'm telling you, God had to be pleased with our faith because we were close to Him, we were dependent on Him, we were desperate for Him, we were walking with Him.

14:34.213 --> 14:38.858
We had what I would call a high view of God, a reverent view of God.

14:38.898 --> 14:43.082
If you were with us last week, we talked about a high view or a low view of God.

14:43.102 --> 14:48.288
A high view of God is, you see God is holy and reverent, high and lifted up.

14:48.308 --> 14:53.874
You want to honor Him, a low view of God, unfortunately is common today when people see God as

14:54.178 --> 14:58.222
casual, and they're almost comfortable around God.

14:58.382 --> 15:01.525
Why does your view of God matter so much?

15:02.246 --> 15:09.012
Because the strength of your faith is a reflection of your view of God.

15:09.032 --> 15:14.257
When you have a high view of God, you'll have big and strong and growing faith.

15:14.978 --> 15:19.442
But a low view of God leads to these three types of faith.

15:20.083 --> 15:23.666
A low view of God leads to conditional faith,

15:24.162 --> 15:32.971
A low view of God leads to stagnant faith, and a low view of God leads to what I call safe faith.

15:34.973 --> 15:37.515
Is your faith pleasing to God?

15:38.937 --> 15:45.764
Or do you have conditional faith, conditional faith?

15:46.404 --> 15:48.046
It's so common today.

15:48.947 --> 15:51.890
This is the kind of faith that says, God, I'll trust you.

15:52.610 --> 15:54.893
as long as you do what I think you should.

15:54.913 --> 16:00.680
And if God doesn't do what we wanted to do, we don't just feel disappointed.

16:00.700 --> 16:01.801
Sometimes we feel betrayed.

16:01.821 --> 16:04.685
I want to tell you right now, that's not real faith.

16:05.566 --> 16:06.447
That's control.

16:08.089 --> 16:09.971
And we do it all the time.

16:10.752 --> 16:18.602
You're a kid and you're praying for your mom and dad's marriage, believing that it's going to be saved and it's not, and your faith falls apart.

16:19.843 --> 16:22.226
We pray for a loved one to be healed.

16:22.882 --> 16:24.685
and they're not.

16:24.705 --> 16:32.596
Or you pray some specific prayer that you get that job or get to date that girl or go to that school and you say, but God, I did everything right.

16:33.838 --> 16:38.224
And when it doesn't happen, your faith suddenly feels fragile.

16:39.666 --> 16:40.027
Why?

16:40.067 --> 16:45.474
Because you had your faith in the outcome, not your faith in God.

16:48.499 --> 16:50.802
You see, God pleasing faith.

16:51.554 --> 16:54.096
Isn't trusting God to do what we want?

16:55.378 --> 16:59.622
God pleasing faith is trusting God even when he doesn't.

17:01.183 --> 17:04.166
It's a low view of God, conditional faith.

17:04.206 --> 17:07.669
It also leads to what I call stagnant faith.

17:08.130 --> 17:09.611
And this is common as well.

17:10.352 --> 17:12.574
I mean, this has been me.

17:13.455 --> 17:14.776
This is maybe some of you right now.

17:15.517 --> 17:18.139
Stagnant faith isn't dead, it's just stuck.

17:19.361 --> 17:20.882
It's not that you've,

17:20.994 --> 17:25.320
lost your belief, it's just that your faith has stopped growing.

17:26.802 --> 17:34.533
And what happens is you can still like show up, you still check the boxes, you still serve, you still come and you even lift your hands at the right point because you know you're supposed to do that.

17:34.553 --> 17:38.358
But deep down, you know that your passion for God has faded.

17:40.081 --> 17:42.784
For me, it was a lack of spiritual urgency.

17:44.126 --> 17:46.770
It's a void of spiritual hunger.

17:47.650 --> 17:55.559
And the most dangerous thing about stagnant faith is that what doesn't grow eventually dies.

17:57.300 --> 17:59.102
It's a love you of God.

17:59.122 --> 18:00.344
I got another big deal.

18:00.364 --> 18:01.105
I can take God to leave.

18:01.125 --> 18:03.407
I mean, it got me, you know, it got my home more.

18:03.787 --> 18:13.278
You know, it got the big guy upstairs and at least to a conditional faith or a stagnant faith or a safe faith.

18:13.298 --> 18:14.759
And what does a safe faith do?

18:15.580 --> 18:17.362
Well, a safe faith

18:17.986 --> 18:19.047
avoids risks.

18:20.929 --> 18:23.152
A safe faith refuses to step out.

18:24.553 --> 18:26.215
A safe faith hedges.

18:27.917 --> 18:31.240
I found myself praying what I call hedging prayers.

18:32.181 --> 18:35.765
God, I hope you do, but I'm not sure you will.

18:36.246 --> 18:39.830
And so if you don't, I've given God a way out.

18:40.310 --> 18:42.112
Safe faith always has a plan B.

18:43.173 --> 18:47.538
And safe faith, and this is, I've been here for too many seasons,

18:47.874 --> 18:51.277
It's dangerous because of safe faith whispers.

18:51.337 --> 18:52.118
You're doing fine.

18:52.138 --> 18:53.920
You're doing fine.

18:53.960 --> 18:59.385
But the church that pleases God, our goal is not to do fine.

18:59.425 --> 19:02.609
Our goal is to live by faith.

19:03.770 --> 19:04.490
To live by faith.

19:05.271 --> 19:06.072
And here's a problem.

19:06.973 --> 19:16.242
If you're living with a safe faith right now, you have to understand, you cannot play it safe and please God.

19:18.306 --> 19:21.630
because it's impossible to please God without faith.

19:22.932 --> 19:32.924
When you go back to the early years, men, I'm telling you, I get so emotional because it is impossible to describe the faith risks that we took.

19:33.044 --> 19:37.369
You go all the way back to the very first weekend and I mean, we had nothing.

19:37.509 --> 19:40.152
We had no phone line back when there's a land line.

19:40.172 --> 19:42.235
If you don't know what that is, you don't know what overhead projector is either.

19:42.615 --> 19:43.476
You know, nothing.

19:43.496 --> 19:44.978
I mean, nothing, nothing.

19:45.154 --> 19:57.225
And we had the very first offering, and I looked out there, I knew most people, but there was a guy that looked out, and I didn't know him, and he looked like he had had not just a hard week, but a hard life.

19:58.827 --> 20:03.431
And I'm sitting there like, really praying God, help us have a good offering, please, first offering God, please.

20:04.032 --> 20:08.316
And I felt prompted in that moment to do something I wasn't planning on doing.

20:08.917 --> 20:11.259
And I thought, I don't want to do that.

20:11.799 --> 20:14.642
And I said, okay,

20:15.298 --> 20:24.750
If you're here and you have a need for like food or someplace to stay and you don't have, as the offering bucket comes by, you can take back out.

20:25.891 --> 20:29.856
And I said that on the first weekend when we had nothing.

20:31.498 --> 20:42.111
And 30 years later, God has honored that moment of faith and provided through and through and through beyond anything that we ever imagined.

20:42.431 --> 20:44.594
It was a faith moment, take for me.

20:45.474 --> 20:45.975
My heart.

20:47.437 --> 20:51.102
We moved from the little garage to a middle school.

20:51.823 --> 20:55.589
We're so excited to have a place that you could fit more than 40 people.

20:56.470 --> 21:02.780
And the custodian there, his name was Paul, and we led Paul to Christ, and he was so excited to be part of the church.

21:03.140 --> 21:12.434
And at the end of May, Paul came up to me, and he said, on a Sunday morning, right before the service, oh, I have bad news for you, Craig.

21:12.610 --> 21:14.413
The school board said, you can't meet here anymore.

21:14.453 --> 21:16.576
This is your last week.

21:16.596 --> 21:18.458
He told me 20 minutes before service.

21:18.478 --> 21:19.360
You can't meet here anymore.

21:20.601 --> 21:26.390
And I started crying, sobbing uncontrollably.

21:26.710 --> 21:27.271
There was no place.

21:27.291 --> 21:28.433
We've been searching, searching, searching.

21:28.453 --> 21:29.274
There was no place to be.

21:29.995 --> 21:34.421
And so I stood up at the end of the service and said to everybody there, we don't have any place to meet.

21:34.922 --> 21:36.825
We may be in homes next week, I don't know.

21:37.345 --> 21:40.690
And at that moment, I'm telling you the spirit of God came on me.

21:40.834 --> 21:50.266
And in the middle of saying, we don't know where we're gonna meet, I stepped forward and almost prophetically said, no, actually, God's gonna open up a door and we'll call you.

21:50.286 --> 21:52.648
We didn't text, we didn't email, because we didn't have that stuff.

21:52.849 --> 21:59.357
We'll call you and tell you the place that God opens up next week and the whole church cheered.

21:59.637 --> 22:02.480
And I went home and Amy said, did you just prophesied that?

22:02.561 --> 22:09.729
And I said, I don't know, I might be a false prophet.

22:09.749 --> 22:10.290
Faith.

22:12.130 --> 22:20.820
And Tuesday of that week, someone called me and said, hey, there's this bike factory that they might want to sell.

22:21.061 --> 22:25.326
And I went Tuesday afternoon and looked at the bike factory and thought, we could do church here.

22:25.626 --> 22:31.333
I'm telling you right now, listen to me, on a handshake, no contract, no money.

22:31.833 --> 22:34.677
I shook hands with a man who said he would sell it to us.

22:35.117 --> 22:39.122
Amy and I took out a home equity loan to put down to buy the thing

22:39.234 --> 22:45.611
We met there on a handshake the next Sunday and had three great years of ministry in the bike factory to the glory of God.

22:45.952 --> 22:47.576
Many of you were there.

22:48.839 --> 22:49.842
And then...

22:50.562 --> 23:00.093
The faith, the faith, the faith one day to maybe build a real and permanent church, and we had the faith to build the Life Church Oklahoma City campus.

23:00.153 --> 23:06.019
The great thing about that sign is my name is misspelled horribly, not even close, but it is a hard name to spell.

23:06.520 --> 23:15.570
And we built that building, 600 people, and oddly, it was full once, twice, three times, four times, five times, six times, and then suddenly,

23:15.746 --> 23:22.593
We were turning people away and Pastor Sam Roberts, I think it was Pastor Sam, said, what if we did search in another location?

23:23.393 --> 23:24.755
This was 1999.

23:25.055 --> 23:28.118
That was not a thing.

23:28.778 --> 23:30.600
To my knowledge, it had never been done.

23:31.601 --> 23:40.009
And we had the faith to do it at one location and then to be at an AMC movie theater where it was amazing, you could get saved by Jesus.

23:40.149 --> 23:43.593
And if you could hide for an hour, you could stick around and see a movie for free.

23:44.113 --> 23:45.074
All at the same.

23:45.986 --> 23:46.547
place.

23:47.748 --> 23:53.156
And then the year 2000, how many of you remember Y2K if you weren't born then?

23:53.196 --> 23:54.317
It's a great time not to be born.

23:54.618 --> 24:02.668
The members of this church called Metro Church called us and essentially through some conversations decided to merge with us.

24:03.029 --> 24:07.855
And the building that I'm preaching in was actually another church that joined us.

24:08.336 --> 24:11.260
The faith to merge church is something that had never been done.

24:11.480 --> 24:15.666
And then very next weekend, when I was supposed to preach there, Amy gave birth.

24:15.906 --> 24:16.387
Why?

24:16.747 --> 24:19.410
Because every time I looked at her, she got pregnant.

24:20.311 --> 24:24.576
And she gave birth to Sam between Saturday night and Sunday morning.

24:25.237 --> 24:29.622
And so we thought we'd always wonder what would happen if we showed a video message.

24:29.962 --> 24:31.384
And everybody said it would never work.

24:31.624 --> 24:33.086
And so we had the faith to try.

24:33.487 --> 24:34.288
And we had to.

24:34.468 --> 24:36.670
Because if I had priests, I might not be married.

24:36.690 --> 24:38.132
But we had the faith to try.

24:38.152 --> 24:40.034
And we ran the video teaching.

24:40.235 --> 24:41.696
And more people got saved.

24:41.916 --> 24:43.218
And that service, and even

24:43.266 --> 24:47.450
And then we thought to ourselves, what if we tried that in locations?

24:47.750 --> 24:51.373
And we had about 100 people driving in from Tulsa, Oklahoma.

24:51.393 --> 24:53.115
And they said, could we start a church there?

24:53.335 --> 25:07.547
And so Pastor Kevin and Pastor Bobby would take a VCR tape after Saturday night, drive over to a holiday inn in a ballroom called the Mohawk Room and plug it into a TV with 100 people and started what eventually became the Tulsa campus.

25:07.807 --> 25:13.252
And then from there, someone had the courage and the faith to start in still water, Oklahoma.

25:13.232 --> 25:15.856
And then South Oklahoma City.

25:16.097 --> 25:18.240
And then the faith started in Fort Worth, Texas.

25:18.681 --> 25:20.865
If you're clapping now, you're going to be clapping for a while.

25:21.165 --> 25:22.748
And then Hendersonville, Tennessee.

25:23.048 --> 25:25.412
And then Life Search Online came up.

25:25.432 --> 25:26.895
And then Wellington, Florida.

25:26.915 --> 25:28.056
Albany, New York.

25:28.077 --> 25:29.218
North Oklahoma City.

25:29.539 --> 25:30.701
South Tulsa, Oklahoma.

25:31.001 --> 25:32.344
Owaso, Oklahoma.

25:32.364 --> 25:33.465
You've got Oklahoma.

25:33.485 --> 25:34.607
Midwest City, Oklahoma.

25:34.687 --> 25:35.829
I'm from Oklahoma, by the way.

25:36.010 --> 25:37.672
Broken Arrow, Oklahoma.

25:37.692 --> 25:38.674
Jeez, Oklahoma.

25:39.458 --> 25:56.384
Keller, Texas, more Oklahoma, Broadway in Britain, Wichita, Kansas, Rio Rancho, New Mexico, Saunee, Oklahoma, South Broken Arrow, Mustang, Fort Smith, Overland Park, Norman, Catusa, Omaha, Rogers, Springfield, no wonder I'm tired.

25:56.625 --> 26:02.514
West Wichita, Northland, Mansfield, Texas, Colorado Springs, Lenexa,

26:02.754 --> 26:12.830
East Kansas City, Des Moines, McKinney, Texas, South Denver, Derby, Kansas, Amarillo, Texas, Austin, Texas, North Denver, West Palm Beach, Florida, and guess what?

26:13.511 --> 26:17.577
More to come this year for the glory of God.

26:17.597 --> 26:19.500
Because we're just getting started.

26:19.520 --> 26:20.922
Just getting started.

26:20.942 --> 26:21.824
Just getting started.

26:22.044 --> 26:31.058
In the early years, in the early years, in the early years, Jesus would have been amazed by my faith.

26:33.698 --> 26:34.499
Until he wasn't.

26:37.844 --> 26:38.464
Until he wasn't.

26:40.988 --> 26:47.477
Because I'm gonna tell you right now, it's been a fantastic, unbelievable, God glorifying 30 years, and it's been hard.

26:53.024 --> 26:58.171
And midway through, the grind just started to kind of beat me down.

26:59.533 --> 27:03.058
And I got tired of like, living by faith.

27:03.746 --> 27:05.107
and tired of hurting.

27:05.988 --> 27:07.049
And I just didn't want to risk.

27:08.371 --> 27:12.335
And so I started leading with a very, very safe faith.

27:12.355 --> 27:14.617
I started to hedge and play it safe.

27:16.119 --> 27:18.641
The problem is a faith that costs nothing, accomplices nothing.

27:20.563 --> 27:24.147
And the good news is God never let it be easy.

27:25.048 --> 27:30.994
The first seven years, I'm gonna tell you right now, first seven years were harder than I could ever describe.

27:31.810 --> 27:36.217
And it's hard to even say this out loud, but I think the last seven years may have been more difficult.

27:38.221 --> 27:43.430
The good news is because it was difficult, it made me desperate for God again.

27:43.470 --> 27:48.638
Desperate, desperate for God, desperate, desperate.

27:48.919 --> 27:50.702
Like I need you God, I need you God.

27:50.922 --> 27:55.570
Like the big faith kind of prayers like God, if you don't come through, I'm not gonna make it type of prayers.

27:56.610 --> 27:58.693
And I cried out to God again with a desperate type of faith.

27:59.374 --> 28:01.717
Much like the very first Sunday with 40 people there.

28:02.418 --> 28:03.539
And they're at the end of the service.

28:04.040 --> 28:08.326
The room was cold and I was nervous and I felt prompted to share the gospel.

28:08.987 --> 28:09.748
And I didn't want to.

28:10.970 --> 28:11.450
I didn't want to.

28:11.530 --> 28:14.535
Not because I didn't believe, but because I was afraid no one would respond.

28:15.756 --> 28:21.404
And so by faith I closed my eyes and I talked about sin and I talked about a savior.

28:22.405 --> 28:25.810
I said, if you wanna trust him, if you wanna be new, if you wanna be forgiven, lift your hands.

28:30.114 --> 28:38.234
On the day there were seven people, seven people, seven people on the very first day, seven people, seven people, seven people, seven people, seven people who crossed from death to life.

28:40.961 --> 28:42.244
And I cried all the way home.

28:42.685 --> 28:46.414
On day number one, I thought if this whole thing was just for one, it would be worth it.

28:46.515 --> 28:47.858
And that's why I want to tell you

28:48.194 --> 28:52.219
that my faith is big again, my faith is big again, my faith for the one.

28:52.279 --> 28:58.606
I'm telling you right now, I have never cared about the one more than I do at this moment right now, my faith for the one is big again.

28:58.926 --> 29:02.190
And sometimes people say, but the church has gotten so big and it's too big.

29:02.230 --> 29:09.598
I'm gonna tell you right now, just so you'll hear it from me, as long as there's one person in this world that does not know Christ.

29:09.658 --> 29:13.783
This church is not too big, it's never too big to the glory of God.

29:14.503 --> 29:16.786
We're just getting started.

29:17.122 --> 29:18.684
We're just getting started.

29:19.665 --> 29:21.747
And so, what kind of church are we gonna be?

29:21.767 --> 29:23.489
We're gonna be a church that pleases God.

29:23.509 --> 29:26.773
To be a church that pleases God, it's gotta be filled with people pleasing God.

29:26.793 --> 29:31.978
So I'm gonna ask you right now, is your faith pleasing to God?

29:33.840 --> 29:36.623
Because the faith that pleases God is never conditional.

29:38.165 --> 29:39.486
It's never stagnant.

29:40.628 --> 29:43.391
It's never safe.

29:43.411 --> 29:46.514
If you find yourself like I have,

29:46.594 --> 29:48.797
to have it a lower view of God.

29:50.078 --> 29:51.300
And it's limited your faith.

29:51.340 --> 29:54.764
I want you to see God as he is.

29:56.045 --> 29:56.986
See him as he is.

29:58.148 --> 29:59.329
Who is your God?

30:00.630 --> 30:01.632
He's your savior.

30:03.274 --> 30:04.735
Who saves you from your sense.

30:06.457 --> 30:07.378
He's your redeemer.

30:08.500 --> 30:11.543
Who made you new when you thought you were too far gone.

30:12.885 --> 30:13.906
He's your comforter.

30:14.594 --> 30:17.137
with you every moment that your heart is heavy.

30:18.178 --> 30:21.361
He's your rock when everything else is shaking.

30:22.462 --> 30:27.507
Our God is our fortress, a safe hiding place.

30:28.629 --> 30:32.012
He's your strength when you don't have any left.

30:33.213 --> 30:34.415
Our God is your healer.

30:34.755 --> 30:40.561
It's a hobo rock in your body, healing your body, healing your heart, healing your mind, healing you from your past.

30:40.581 --> 30:41.522
He's your defender.

30:42.402 --> 30:44.865
fighting you in battles that you don't even see.

30:46.227 --> 30:50.953
He is your peace that passes all understanding when you feel anxious and afraid.

30:51.974 --> 30:56.119
He is your hope when the future seems uncertain.

30:56.139 --> 31:00.305
He is your ever-present help in time of trouble right now.

31:02.007 --> 31:04.189
In this moment, that's who he is.

31:05.231 --> 31:11.058
When you see him like that, I am lifted up, irreverent in a holy God.

31:12.034 --> 31:15.501
Your faith grows knowing that all things are possible of God.

31:16.383 --> 31:25.523
And so I declare now to Him, now to Him who is able to do a measurably more than all we can ask or imagine according to His power.

31:25.543 --> 31:28.710
But does it work within us, within you, within us, within you?

31:28.770 --> 31:32.498
Now to Him be the glory where in the church

31:32.578 --> 31:37.045
in Christ Jesus through all generations forever and ever.

31:37.205 --> 31:46.821
May He get the glory and the people of God said amen and amen because the church that pleases God will be a faith filled church.

31:46.841 --> 31:53.451
So if your faith has shrunk or if you've lost your faith, repent.

31:54.613 --> 31:55.395
Believe again.

31:55.435 --> 31:57.558
Trust again.

31:57.618 --> 32:00.082
Step out in faith.

32:00.610 --> 32:02.753
Believe that he hears the cries of your heart.

32:03.474 --> 32:06.258
Believe that when you draw near to him, he draws near to you.

32:06.318 --> 32:08.702
Believe him to heal.

32:09.042 --> 32:11.947
Believe him to save those that you love.

32:12.628 --> 32:16.133
Believe him to break you free from the addiction that holds you back.

32:16.754 --> 32:23.844
Believe that the same spirit that raised Christ from the dead dwells within you, calling you to do good works which glorify him.

32:24.125 --> 32:28.311
Believe him enough to take the step of faith and obey what he calls you to do.

32:29.693 --> 32:30.354
Believe.

32:30.818 --> 32:38.226
They can use you, use me, use us, His church, to lead people to become fully devoted followers of Christ.

32:38.246 --> 32:51.080
I'll tell you right now, this church was built by faith and the future of this church, God's church, will be built by people who still have faith that God can do more, will do more, and will be glorified when He does.

32:51.100 --> 32:52.882
It's His church and He gets the glory.

32:53.502 --> 32:56.946
So father, thank you for 30 years.

32:58.018 --> 33:02.584
And God, we believe by your power, we're just getting started today as your praying church, nobody looking around.

33:02.944 --> 33:11.435
Those of you who are believers, you are a follower of Jesus, you've been baptized, you're in the church as a church, and you wanna honor God with your faith.

33:11.475 --> 33:14.339
You may look at your life right now and be where I've been.

33:14.379 --> 33:24.271
You've been living with conditional faith, where your faith is stagnant, or you're playing it safe in your faith.

33:25.052 --> 33:26.674
You cannot, please.

33:26.850 --> 33:28.411
God without faith.

33:29.212 --> 33:30.654
You say, God help build my faith.

33:30.734 --> 33:32.075
I want to honor you with faith.

33:32.095 --> 33:35.819
I don't care how faith they're strong as I hope you pray this prayer, God, I build my faith.

33:35.959 --> 33:36.920
I want to honor you with faith.

33:36.940 --> 33:43.726
If you're praying that today, would you lift up your hands all over the place right now, lifted up all of our churches, lift your hands up high online, type in the comments section.

33:43.746 --> 33:46.689
I want to honor God with faith and Holy Spirit, we pray.

33:46.729 --> 33:51.714
We know that faith comes by hearing and hearing by the Word of God and your Word has been spoken today.

33:51.734 --> 33:52.575
So build our faith.

33:53.476 --> 33:56.018
God, build our faith to do what you call us to do.

33:56.450 --> 34:15.170
individually and corporately, as your church, the body of Christ, we don't go to church, we are the church, we exist for the world, God in power, your church to do your will, your work on earth, as it is in heaven, God build my faith to believe for more, build our faith to know that all things are possible with you.

34:16.551 --> 34:21.817
God help us to be a faith filled church that pleases you.

34:21.837 --> 34:23.058
As you keep praying today,

34:23.586 --> 34:31.096
There are those of you that are here just like seven people on the first Sunday who didn't know where they stood with God.

34:32.198 --> 34:34.401
And if I ask you right now, like, are you certain?

34:34.501 --> 34:44.495
Do you know beyond a shadow of a doubt that you're right with God, that you're in fellowship with Him, that if you die, do you know for sure you go to heaven?

34:45.456 --> 34:47.178
And if you don't, let me tell you the same thing.

34:47.198 --> 34:52.946
I've been saying for 30 years, every service, every single week that we've all said, I have, you have.

34:53.122 --> 34:54.946
with all sin, and that's why you feel guilty.

34:55.687 --> 34:58.032
And our sin separates us from the Holy God.

34:58.874 --> 35:01.058
But our God still loves you more than you can imagine.

35:01.098 --> 35:08.914
In fact, His scripture says that for God so loved the world, He so loved you, that He sent His one and only Son, Jesus.

35:09.058 --> 35:11.922
Jesus didn't come to condemn, but he came to save.

35:11.962 --> 35:14.104
He didn't come for those who are already righteous.

35:14.405 --> 35:15.506
He came for the lost.

35:15.806 --> 35:20.032
And Jesus gave his life and God raised him from the dead so that you could be saved.

35:20.112 --> 35:23.196
And we are not saved by our own works, the Bible says.

35:23.556 --> 35:24.717
We can't be good enough.

35:25.038 --> 35:25.839
How are we saved?

35:25.859 --> 35:32.888
The only way we're saved is by grace, the grace of God, the forgiveness of God through faith.

35:34.049 --> 35:38.034
It's impossible to please God without faith.

35:38.402 --> 35:41.591
If you don't know where you stand with God today, we're going to step away from our sin.

35:41.611 --> 35:44.500
We're going to call out on the name of Jesus by faith.

35:44.761 --> 35:46.907
And the Bible says, when you do, God hears your prayers.

35:47.248 --> 35:48.271
He forgives your sins.

35:48.512 --> 35:49.234
The scripture says,

35:49.346 --> 35:57.415
Anyone, and this includes you, doesn't matter what you've done, who calls on the name of the Lord, will be saved today at all of our churches, all of the world online.

35:57.475 --> 35:59.738
Those who say, I don't know where I stand, but I'm ready.

35:59.938 --> 36:00.859
I need His forgiveness.

36:00.939 --> 36:01.880
I want His peace.

36:02.120 --> 36:03.001
I need His grace.

36:03.021 --> 36:04.123
I step away from my sin.

36:04.443 --> 36:06.025
Jesus, I give you my life.

36:06.045 --> 36:08.047
As you surrender to Him, He'll forgive you.

36:08.427 --> 36:09.949
All your sins, He'll make you new.

36:09.989 --> 36:10.910
That's your prayer today.

36:10.990 --> 36:14.354
By faith, Jesus, I surrender my life.

36:14.530 --> 36:16.252
I'm not playing all in.

36:16.593 --> 36:17.815
I give my life to you.

36:17.975 --> 36:19.116
Take my life, Jesus.

36:19.357 --> 36:19.837
I give it to you.

36:19.857 --> 36:20.538
That's your prayer.

36:20.558 --> 36:21.960
Lift your hands high right now.

36:22.201 --> 36:22.782
All over the place.

36:23.162 --> 36:24.063
Praise God for you there.

36:24.344 --> 36:26.006
Right up there, up there, up there.

36:26.126 --> 36:27.628
I'll praise God for the others of you.

36:27.648 --> 36:28.249
Right back over there.

36:28.269 --> 36:30.172
Lift your hand and I say, Jesus, I surrender.

36:30.212 --> 36:31.794
Right back over there.

36:31.814 --> 36:32.816
Oh, praise God.

36:32.836 --> 36:36.020
Others today say, yes, Jesus, I surrender to you.

36:36.040 --> 36:36.821
Right back over here.

36:37.302 --> 36:37.963
I'll come on church.

36:38.043 --> 36:39.345
Give the glory to God today.

36:40.146 --> 36:42.209
Online, just type it in the comment section.

36:42.229 --> 36:43.090
I'm surrendering.

36:43.266 --> 36:47.270
My life to Jesus, and 30 years we pray the same way.

36:47.290 --> 36:51.134
Pray with me, Heavenly Father, forgive all of my sins.

36:52.575 --> 36:53.736
Jesus saved me.

36:55.158 --> 36:55.938
Make me brand new.

36:57.220 --> 37:04.907
Fill me with your spirit so I could know you and serve you and honor you.

37:06.168 --> 37:07.149
My life is not my own.

37:08.591 --> 37:09.432
I give it all to you.

37:10.653 --> 37:11.954
In Jesus' name I pray.

37:13.090 --> 37:14.252
All God's people said.

37:22.705 --> 37:26.091
We are celebrating with those of you who just made the decision to follow Jesus.

37:26.491 --> 37:29.155
Check out the show notes for helpful resources and next steps.

37:29.776 --> 37:35.826
Remember to head over to life.church slash podcast connect to share a little about yourself and how we can support you.

